the same. You mentioned that you had female relatives who may

00:14:35.310 --> 00:14:38.310
be younger than you who also had the mutation. Did they,

00:14:38.310 --> 00:14:43.760
&gt;&gt; Well, my one cousin is in the process right now.

00:14:43.760 --> 00:14:45.140
&gt;&gt; I see. I see.

00:14:45.140 --> 00:14:49.810
&gt;&gt; Of scheduling an appointment for surgical

00:14:49.810 --> 00:14:52.550
removal of her ovaries, oophorectomy.

00:14:52.550 --> 00:14:55.820
&gt;&gt; I see. So it sounds like, you

00:14:55.820 --> 00:14:58.300
know, there's, everyone's sort of going to talk

00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:00.630
to their doctor and make these decisions about

00:15:00.630 --> 00:15:02.550
what's the best action to take for themselves.

00:15:02.550 --> 00:15:04.400
&gt;&gt; And she saw a genetic counselor as well.

00:15:04.400 --> 00:15:08.680
&gt;&gt; So I'm also curious to know what else you found out from your genetic

00:15:08.680 --> 00:15:14.710
report. You said you went to 23 in the end. Was, was the BRCA2 mutation,

00:15:14.710 --> 00:15:16.140
the only surprise you found?

00:15:16.140 --> 00:15:19.408
&gt;&gt; Well, I found out that I had a little risk

00:15:19.408 --> 00:15:24.400
for Alzheimer's disease, but I'm not so sure that was accurate.

00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:25.400
&gt;&gt;

00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:25.100
[LAUGH]

00:15:25.100 --> 00:15:29.654
&gt;&gt; I also found that and I have the

00:15:29.654 --> 00:15:35.806
Tay-sachs mutation. And Tay-sachs is another

00:15:35.806 --> 00:15:41.132
Ashkenazi Jewish genetic mutation and

00:15:41.132 --> 00:15:45.756
Since I'm not having any children and my

00:15:45.756 --> 00:15:50.652
husband wasn't a carrier, then I didn't

00:15:50.652 --> 00:15:55.559
really worry about it but I was surprised.

00:15:56.590 --> 00:16:00.800
if you have a pregnancy, and you're

00:16:02.400 --> 00:16:06.958
baby's identified as having Tay-Sachs, the result of

00:16:06.958 --> 00:16:11.410
a Tay-Sachs baby is they die within a couple of years of

00:16:11.410 --> 00:16:16.720
birth. And it's a lipid storage.

00:16:16.720 --> 00:16:18.020
Disease where

00:16:20.170 --> 00:16:25.920
the baby is missing an enzyme that metabolizes a lipid, and this lipid, norm,

00:16:25.920 --> 00:16:28.500
is normally metabolized, but when you have

00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:32.739
the mutation where when you have Tay-Sachs disease.

00:16:34.830 --> 00:16:37.820
the lipid accumulates in the brain.

00:16:37.820 --> 00:16:38.565
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:16:38.565 --> 00:16:40.070
&gt;&gt; And, the baby dies.

00:16:40.070 --> 00:16:45.280
&gt;&gt; Wow. So, although you knew about your, your ancestry, and you knew

00:16:45.280 --> 00:16:50.360
you were, you know, part of this Ashkenazi Jewish population and, or lineage,

00:16:50.360 --> 00:16:55.650
and and, you know, there were maybe certained. certain variants that you may

00:16:55.650 --> 00:16:59.980
carry. You didn't know which ones and this was, you know, news to you,

00:16:59.980 --> 00:17:00.490
to be a carrier was.

